name: AppEncryptionDeclaration.Attributes
desc: Attributes that describe an App Encryption Declarations resource.

items.name: availableOnFrenchStore
items.desc: A Boolean value that indicates the intent to distribute your app on the French App Store.

items.name: codeValue
items.desc: A unique identifier that can be added to your app to associate it with a given declaration.

items.name: containsProprietaryCryptography
items.desc: A Boolean value that indicates your app implements any proprietary encryption algorithms.

items.name: containsThirdPartyCryptography
items.desc: A Boolean value that indicates your app implements any standard encryption algorithms instead of, or in addition to, using or accessing the encryption in Appleâ€™s operating systems.

items.name: documentName
items.desc: The document name of your submitted export compliance documentation.

items.name: documentType
items.desc: The file type of your submitted export compliance documentation.

items.name: documentUrl
items.desc: The URL to the file of your submitted export compliance documentation.

items.name: exempt
items.desc: A Boolean value that indicates your app is exempt based on your use of encryption and the app's availability.

items.name: usesEncryption
items.desc: A Boolean value that indicates whether your app uses, contains, or incorporates cryptography.

items.name: appEncryptionDeclarationState
items.desc: The approval state of your export compliance documentation.

items.name: uploadedDate
items.desc: The date and time you submitted your declaration.
